162
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:03,660
Oh, Tondobayashi, what's going on?

163
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:05,200
Excuse me.

164
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:08,760
Sui, sui, sui, da da da da, sui, kan.

165
00:06:09,940 --> 00:06:12,220
How about a unexpected Don Dengaishi?

166
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:14,440
It's a house that even a top writer can't come up with.

167
00:06:15,460 --> 00:06:18,300
But why do people who aren't criminals have a machine gun?

168
00:06:19,180 --> 00:06:19,620
That's a lie.

169
00:06:19,940 --> 00:06:21,100
No, that's a coincidence.

170
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:23,640
A machine gun fell in the harbor warehouse.

171
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:25,940
When I picked it up, the main character appeared.

172
00:06:27,060 --> 00:06:28,600
The main character is killing the other person.

173
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,120
No, that's right.

174
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:33,340
The other person was wearing a bulletproof vest by chance.

175
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,460
So it's a weapon.

176
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:36,180
Everyone is shot in the head.

177
00:06:37,580 --> 00:06:39,240
So I'm wearing a bulletproof wig.

178
00:06:40,220 --> 00:06:42,140
It's unnatural to buy a simple udon at such a high price.

179
00:06:42,140 --> 00:06:44,360
Yeah, yeah.

180
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:46,200
Why would you go to the harbor and do this?

181
00:06:47,280 --> 00:06:50,000
And why do you think it's a bad idea to buy udon?

182
00:06:50,980 --> 00:06:52,360
It's noisy every day.

183
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:54,780
It's a gag manga, so leave the details alone.

184
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,540
Either way, it's not a manga for Weekly Sapphire.

185
00:06:58,980 --> 00:07:00,280
This manga cannot be published.

186
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:03,500
I'll somehow get it out of the way.

187
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:05,780
No, you can't.

188
00:07:07,660 --> 00:07:10,640
Anyway, Ryo-chan's manga will never be on Weekly Sapphire.

189
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:13,440
This is the final decision at the editorial meeting.

190
00:07:19,060 --> 00:07:20,560
Damn it, Ryusenshi!

191
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:24,520
It seems like a bad thing is a bad thing, so you give up so easily.

192
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:25,880
What are you talking about?

193
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:26,700
It's that easy?

194
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:27,740
Huh?

195
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,040
Stop it, Honda!

196
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,740
What's wrong, Ryo-chan's husband?

197
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:33,840
Look, there.

198
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,620
Oh, you've thrown away a lot of books.

199
