Because it's not published yet.

211
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:06,920
What kind of book did you make?

212
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:09,380
The world's pen tip?

213
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:14,360
The world of the wonderful Bolt and Nat?

214
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:17,100
There's no way a book like this will sell!

215
00:08:17,940 --> 00:08:18,680
Is that so?

216
00:08:19,340 --> 00:08:20,680
It will never sell!

217
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:21,940
I guarantee it.

218
00:08:22,220 --> 00:08:22,920
I knew it.

219
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:26,260
I have to make a book that will sell here.

220
00:08:27,060 --> 00:08:28,940
If I don't do it, I'll be a father.

221
00:08:29,620 --> 00:08:33,360
Hmm, a book that will sell, a book that will sell...

222
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:35,020
Hm? Then it's a manga!

223
00:08:35,460 --> 00:08:36,300
Manga?

224
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:37,920
That's right, you can make a manga magazine.

225
00:08:37,920 --> 00:08:42,340
You're small, but you're the president of a publishing company!

226
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:48,200
Among these published books, the only thing that sells is manga!

227
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:52,260
Manga is read widely by young people, from children to adults.

228
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:59,420
And it's cheap, you can read it anytime, anywhere, and the contents are interesting!

229
00:09:00,140 --> 00:09:02,780
If you publish a manga magazine, you can overcome your father's crisis!

230
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:05,060
I see!

231
00:09:05,460 --> 00:09:06,940
But it's impossible.

232
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:07,920
